Problem Statement 1: Product Requirement and Low-Fidelity Wireframes
Objective: Build a requirements document and UI wireframes for a security product that scans container images.

Deliverables:
Product Requirements Document (PRD):

Description of the product

User stories (e.g., "As a user, I want to see all vulnerable images in my repo.")

Functional requirements

Non-functional requirements

Technical constraints

Low-Fidelity Wireframes:

Use tools like Balsamiq, Figma, or even hand-drawn mockups

Show:

Dashboard with list of images

Filters for severity (Low/Medium/High)

Details page for individual image scan

(Optional) Development Action Items:

Define what features dev team should start with (e.g., “Implement API to fetch vulnerabilities”).

